 131:Core/Src/main.c **** /*
 132:Core/Src/main.c ****  * Resynchronizing frame parser.
 133:Core/Src/main.c ****  *
 134:Core/Src/main.c ****  *   PS_SYNC1   : hunt for 0xAA. Anything else is discarded.
 135:Core/Src/main.c ****  *   PS_SYNC2   : saw 0xAA, expect 0x55. If another 0xAA arrives, stay here
 136:Core/Src/main.c ****  *                (it might be the real start). Any other byte -> hunt again.
 137:Core/Src/main.c ****  *   PS_PAYLOAD : collect 9 bytes. When full, verify CRC over the first 8.
 138:Core/Src/main.c ****  *                On success, update rc and mark link_ok. On CRC failure,
 139:Core/Src/main.c ****  *                discard and resync — a spurious 0xAA 0x55 only costs one frame.
